FBIS4-17087 "drsov077_a_94011" FBIS-SOV-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Lord Owen, Stoltenburg Arrive for Talks on Bosnia Lord Owen, Stoltenburg Arrive for Talks on Bosnia Envoys, Kozyrev Hold News Conference LD2004214594 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 2005 GMT 20 Apr 94 LD2004214594 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Excerpts] The well-known diplomats David Owen and Thorvald Stoltenberg arrived in Moscow today. This evening they had talks with Andrey Kozyrev. [Correspondent Mikhail Aleksandridi] A news conference was held after their talks. [passage omitted] [Aleksandridi] In Thorvald Stoltenberg's opinion, regular consultations between the co-chairmen of the Coordinating Committee and the Russian side had played an important role in the quest for a peaceful solution of the Bosnian problem. However, in the existing situation, David Owen thinks, it is necessary in order to attain this goal to employ a carrot-and-stick policy, that is to combine the threat of armed pressure with the lifting of the anti-Serb sanctions in the event of the Serbs preferring peace to war.
